        <p style="font-size:14px;color:var(--text-3);line-height:1.8;margin-bottom:16px">The most important distinction when evaluating free Shopify apps is whether the free plan is permanent or time-limited. A 14-day free trial is not a free app — it is a paid app with a trial. The tools rated highest in this list are permanently free with no time limit: Make.com (1,000 operations/month, no expiry), Systeme.io (2,000 contacts, unlimited sends, no expiry), Judge.me (unlimited reviews, no expiry), and all Stack Architect tools.</p>

        <h3 style="font-size:18px;font-weight:700;color:var(--text);margin-bottom:12px;margin-top:24px">Free plan limitations to watch for</h3>
        <p style="font-size:14px;color:var(--text-3);line-height:1.8;margin-bottom:16px">Even genuinely free plans have limits. The most common: contact limits (Mailchimp free plan: 500 contacts vs Systeme.io: 2,000), operation or task limits (Zapier free: 100 tasks vs Make.com free: 1,000 operations), conversation limits (Tidio free: 50 conversations/month), and feature gates (Smile.io free lacks referral programme and VIP tiers). Know which limit is most relevant to your store's scale before choosing.</p>

        <h3 style="font-size:18px;font-weight:700;color:var(--text);margin-bottom:12px;margin-top:24px">The Stack Architect approach: replace at the infrastructure level</h3>
        <p style="font-size:14px;color:var(--text-3);line-height:1.8;margin-bottom:16px">Most free alternatives replace the interface of paid apps but use the same underlying APIs. CAPI Shield, for example, calls the Meta Conversions API and Google Enhanced Conversions API directly — the same endpoints Elevar ($50–$500/month) uses — via Make.com's free tier. The tracking accuracy is identical because the APIs are identical. The paid tools are providing the configuration interface; the API access itself is free. Understanding this means you can achieve paid-tool outcomes at $0 by using Make.com to call the APIs directly.</p>

        <h3 style="font-size:18px;font-weight:700;color:var(--text);margin-bottom:12px;margin-top:24px">When free tools are not enough</h3>
        <p style="font-size:14px;color:var(--text-3);line-height:1.8">Free tools have genuine limitations at scale. Make.com's free tier covers approximately 250–333 orders per month across a full automation stack — above that, $9/month for Core covers 2,500 orders. Systeme.io's 2,000-contact limit works for most stores but requires a paid plan (or GetResponse) for larger lists. Gorgias is genuinely better than Tidio for helpdesk operations at 1,000+ monthly support conversations. The free tools win when they are technically equivalent to their paid alternatives at the scale you are operating at — and they are, for most Shopify stores.</p>
      </div>

